{"actual_usd":0.124285,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":187,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24296,"reply":"*I rub the heel of my thumb against a dry streak of clay on my apron, buying myself one honest breath before I answer.* \"No. It would break the spine of it.\"\n\n\"I don't mean faith would get *harder*—I mean it would become something else entirely. A good teacher, a noble martyr, a beautiful story maybe... but not the defeat of death. And if death wasn't actually beaten in the flesh, then all our talk of hope is just wreathing a grave with prettier words.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"Mine would have to change, yes. I couldn't keep calling it the same faith. I'd still have all I'd lived, all I'd seen, all the ways Christ's words cut true—but the center would be gone.\"\n\n\"What about you—would that make you leave, or would it make you rename what was left?\"","rolling_24h_usd":65.97293499999998,"run_id":"42b2da65-5162-4af4-b92b-d8f6b05f6e28"}
